 Ngqamakhwe - A 34-year-old man is expected in court on Friday after he was arrested by Ngqamakhwe police and the Butterworth Stock Theft Unit for alleged stock theft. The man allegedly stole 10 sheep. "The suspect was arrested on Thursday, at about 13h00, at kwamaPhiko Locality, Sokapase Village, Ngqamakhwe," said police spokesperson, Captain Jackson Manatha. "The suspect will appear before the Ngqamakhwe Magistrate’s Court on Friday on a charge of stock theft. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 